  "description": "A sparrow similar in size/structure to GRSP with the flat head and the large bill.\u00a0 Streaky. \n\r\nFace buffy.\u00a0 Lower back side of auricular patch has two dark spots.\u00a0 No eyestripe.\u00a0 Crown ochre toned with dark bown streaks.\u00a0 No median stripe on the crown.\u00a0 Throat white with double mustache lines. Back of neck buffy with dark brown streaks..\n\r\nUndersides grayish white with upper chest streaked.\u00a0 \n\r\nSong distinctive - a trilly deet-deet-dee-dee - downward slurred.",
